definition: to count/to count as/to regard as/to enumerate (sb's shortcomings)

sentences.english: You can add a prime factor by clicking on the corresponding button.
sentences.chinese: 您可以通過點擊相對應的按鈕來添加一個質因數。

sentences.english: You have to enter all prime factors of the number.
sentences.chinese: 您需要輸入該數字的所有質因數。

sentences.english: The chosen prime factors will be shown in the input field.
sentences.chinese: 被選擇的質因數將會在輸入框顯示出來。

sentences.english: The qualitative factor Q of series resonant circuit for voltage withstanding test is analyzed.
sentences.chinese: 對串聯諧振耐壓試驗迴路的品質因數Q進行了分析。

sentences.english: Click the 'Backspace' button to remove the last entered prime factor.
sentences.chinese: 點擊“退格”鍵可刪除最近輸入的質因數。

sentences.english: Quanlity factor Q is an important parameter for use in radiation protection.
sentences.chinese: 品質因數Q是輻射防護規定中的一個重要參數。
